<p>Clearly, this is still not setting the author. But I want to see if it executes first
and then we'll worry about setting the author.</p>
<h2 id="who-is-i-in-a-scenario">Who is "I" in a Scenario? <a class="headerlink" href="get-authenticated-user#who-is-i-in-a-scenario" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Cool! It runs... and fails because anonymous <em>is</em> still shown on the page. The question
now is: how do we get the current user? The step says "I author". But who is "I" in this
case? In <code>product_admin.feature</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="88c42ae944">
