</p>
<p>You can see that "I" is whomever we logged in as. We didn't specify what the username
should be for that user, but whoever is logged in is who "I" represents.</p>
<p>When we worked with the <code>ls</code> scenarios earlier, we needed to share the command output
string between the steps of a scenario. In this case, we have a similar need: we
need to share the user object from the step where we log in, with the step where
"I" author some products. To share data between steps, create a new <code>private $currentUser;</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="100d047bcd">
